Nearby, alumni volunteers provide quick pep talks around the coffee station, while the engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage. International students queue specifically for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. Throughout the event, representatives from nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths, and an alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews. Career counselors remind attendees to maintain eye contact. As the fair progresses, announcement chimes signal the final hour of the event.

An alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews, and a startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, while representatives from nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom. Meanwhile, event staff scan registrations and hand out lanyards at the entrance.
